message.content: Some of the biggest challenges seniors in Jordan face include limited access to quality healthcare and support services, financial constraints and pension issues, social isolation and loneliness, age-related discrimination in employment, lack of suitable housing options, and difficulties in accessing public transportation. Additionally, seniors may also face cultural barriers and lack of awareness about their rights and entitlements, as well as age-related issues such as chronic diseases and disabilities that can further impact their quality of life.
